------------------------------------------------------------
System Overview
------------------------------------------------------------

This project implements an embedded AI-powered IoT agent
running on Realtek Ameba Pro2 platform:

- AMB82-mini
- HUB 8735 Ultra

It integrates:

- Telegram Bot API (HTTPS long polling)
- Google Gemini API (generateContent)
- Gemini multimodal vision reasoning
- Gemini grounded web search
- Prompt-driven JSON tool routing
- Camera capture + image transmission
- GPIO digital / analog output control
- Digital / analog input sensing
- In-memory conversation state management
- FreeRTOS background task scheduling

The system behaves as a hybrid autonomous AI agent:

"Conversation + Reasoning + Tools + Vision + Memory + Hardware"

------------------------------------------------------------
Core Runtime Architecture
------------------------------------------------------------

Telegram User
      ↓
Telegram Polling Task (FreeRTOS)
      ↓
Message Router
(Command / Chat / Gemini Dispatch)
      ↓
Gemini Reasoning Engine
(Chat / Search / Vision / Workflow Planning)
      ↓
Structured JSON tool_call Output
      ↓
ArduinoJson Validation
      ↓
Tool Dispatcher (useTools)
      ↓
Hardware / Vision / Search / Memory Execution
      ↓
Natural Language Feedback to User

NOTE:

This is a prompt-driven orchestration system.

Tool routing decisions are generated by Gemini through
strict JSON output and validated locally before execution.

No native Gemini function-calling API is used.

------------------------------------------------------------
Main Capabilities
------------------------------------------------------------

- Telegram AI chatbot via HTTPS polling
- Natural language assistant (Gemini 3 Flash)
- Prompt-based tool execution routing
- Real-time grounded web search
- Camera still capture + Telegram upload
- Multimodal image understanding
- Digital output control (0 or 1)
- Analog output control (0–255)
- Digital input reading
- Analog sensor reading
- Runtime memory diagnostics
- In-memory conversation persistence
- Automatic workflow continuation
- WiFi auto-reconnection recovery
- FreeRTOS concurrent polling

------------------------------------------------------------
Supported Telegram Commands
------------------------------------------------------------

/help
Show available commands

/digitalwrite
Set digital output (0 or 1)

/analogwrite
Set analog output (0–255)

/digitalread
Read digital input pin

/analogread
Read analog input pin

/still
Capture image and send to Telegram

/vision
Capture and analyze image

/search
Grounded web search

/memory
Show runtime memory status

/reset
Reset conversation memory

------------------------------------------------------------
Tool Calling Mechanism
------------------------------------------------------------

Gemini is instructed through system prompt constraints
to emit ONLY valid JSON tool_call structures whenever
tool execution is required.

Key design principles:

- Prompt-based function routing
- Strict schema enforcement
- Local JSON validation
- Explicit execution sequencing
- No simulated hardware execution

------------------------------------------------------------
Tool Format Specification
------------------------------------------------------------

1. Digital Output

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/digitalwrite",
  "params": {
    "pin": "<GPIO>",
    "pinmode": "digitalwrite",
    "value": 1 | 0
  }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

2. Analog Output

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/analogwrite",
  "params": {
    "pin": "<GPIO>",
    "pinmode": "analogwrite",
    "value": 0-255
  }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

3. Digital Input

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/digitalread",
  "params": {
    "pin": "<GPIO>",
    "pinmode": "digitalread"
  }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

4. Analog Input

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/analogread",
  "params": {
    "pin": "<GPIO>",
    "pinmode": "analogread"
  }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

5. Camera Capture

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/still",
  "params": {}
}

------------------------------------------------------------

6. Vision Analysis

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/vision",
  "params": {
    "query": "<analysis request>"
  }
}

Capture occurs before multimodal reasoning.

------------------------------------------------------------

7. Grounded Search

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/search",
  "params": {
    "query": "<search query>"
  }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

8. Memory Control

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/memory" | "/reset",
  "params": {}
}

------------------------------------------------------------

9. Conversational Reply

{
  "type": "tool_call",
  "method": "/chat",
  "params": {
    "reply": "<natural language reply>"
  }
}

------------------------------------------------------------
Execution Flow
------------------------------------------------------------

1. Telegram receives message
2. Router classifies request:

   - Direct tool command
   - Natural language reasoning request

3. Gemini processes context
4. Gemini emits tool_call JSON
5. ArduinoJson validates structure
6. useTools() executes action:

   - GPIO control
   - Sensor read
   - Camera capture
   - Vision analysis
   - Grounded search
   - Memory operation
   - Telegram output

7. Execution result is injected into runtime memory
8. Gemini generates natural-language follow-up
9. Final response is sent to user

------------------------------------------------------------
Sequential Task Enforcement
------------------------------------------------------------

For multi-step workflows:

1. Gather external information
2. Analyze completion condition
3. Ask for missing parameters
4. Request user confirmation
5. Execute hardware action
6. Report final state

The model is forbidden from skipping steps
or fabricating completed hardware actions.

------------------------------------------------------------
Hardware Platform
------------------------------------------------------------

Supported Boards:

- AMB82-mini
- HUB 8735 Ultra

Features:

- WiFi 802.11
- Integrated camera
- GPIO digital I/O
- GPIO analog I/O
- Hardware button input
